<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Former Fold" class="currentChild" href="Former_Fold">Former Fold</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
On a <a title="Web Press" href="Web_Press">web press</a>, a fold created by an in-line folder (called a <a title="former folder" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/former_folder">former folder</a>). A former fold is essentially a single fold made parallel to the direction of web travel, created as the web is pulled over a triangular metal <a title="Former Board" href="Former_Board">former board</a>. The former fold is usually the first fold made, and, depending on the application, a former fold may be the only fold required. A former fold is also called a <a title="Newspaper Fold" href="Newspaper_Fold">newspaper fold</a> or a <a title="Plow Fold" href="Plow_Fold">plow fold</a>. See also <a title="Jaw Fold" href="Jaw_Fold">Jaw Fold</a> and <a title="Chopper Fold" href="Chopper_Fold">Chopper Fold</a>. 
</p>
